    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm running a linear regression on some housing market data but my residuals aren't looking normal at all. the distribution is all skewed and i've got some weird outliers messing with the fit. what are my best options to fix this?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When your residuals are skewed and have outliers, you have several options to address the non-normality in your linear regression. You could try transforming your dependent variable, such as using a log or square root transformation, which often helps normalize the distribution. Alternatively, you might consider using robust regression methods, which are less sensitive to the influence of outliers. You could also investigate the outliers themselves to see if they represent genuine extreme cases or data entry errors that need correction.",
      "source": "target",
